Death/Suicide Implicit Association Task: overall d-score (non-weighted mean of the 2 d-scores); main DV
Notes: Suggested interpretation: Less than or equal to -0.65= ''a strong'' preference for hypothesis-NONconforming pairings; Less than -0.35= ''a moderate'' preference for hypothesis-NONconforming pairings; Less than -0.15= ''a slight'' preference for hypothesis-NONforming pairings; Between -0.15 and 0.15= ''little to no'' preference; Greater than 0.15= ''a slight'' preference for hypothesis-conforming pairings; Greater than 0.35= ''a moderate'' preference for hypothesis-conforming pairings; Greater than 0.65= ''a strong'' preference for hypothesis-conforming pairings
